  "prompt": "What percentage of freshers are accepted into the IIM's every year?",
  "response": "The percentage of freshers admitted to Indian Institutes of Management (IIMs) can vary year by year and can differ across individual IIMs. Generally speaking, freshers (those with no prior full-time work experience) make up a significant portion of the incoming batch each year. Historically, freshers can make up around 20% to 30% of the batch, but this can fluctuate based on various factors such as the admission policies of the specific IIM, the strength and performance of the pool of applicants, and other considerations like diversity objectives.\n\nFor precise and up-to-date statistics on the percentage of freshers accepted, it is best to consult the official admission reports or websites of the individual IIMs for the most accurate information.",
